The paper discusses the integration of electrochemical metallization cell (ECM) nanodevices with tunable filamentary switching in nanoscale learning systems. This topic is related to neural networks and neuromorphic computing, which are typically categorized under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also discusses the properties of memristive nanodevices, which are related to electronic devices and materials, and can be categorized under cs.ET (Emerging Technologies). The paper also discusses the integration of ECM nanodevices with learning architectures, which can be categorized under cs.AR (Hardware Architecture). The paper also discusses the use of ECM nanodevices for solving classification tasks, which can be categorized under cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper discusses the benefits and drawbacks of the proposed learning architectures, which can be categorized under cs.EM (Electronic Materials).
